<item>
            <title>[SPARK-29000] [SQL] Decimal precision overflow when don&apos;t allow precision loss</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-29000</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When we set spark.sql.decimalOperations.allowPrecisionLoss=false.&lt;br/&gt;
For the sql below, the result will overflow and return null.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Some comments here
&lt;/span&gt;select &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; when 1=2 then 1 &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; 100.000000000000000000000000 end * 1
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, this sql will return correct result.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Some comments here
&lt;/span&gt;select &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; when 1=2 then 1 &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; 100.000000000000000000000000 end * 1.0
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
